<item>
            <title>[JCR-2774] Access control for repository level API operations</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-2774</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>it is a open issue (i guess since jackrabbit 1.0) that the repository level write operations lack any kind of permission check.&lt;br/&gt;
this issues has been raised during specification of jsr 283 [1] but didn&amp;#39;t made it into the specification (left to implementation).&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
in jackrabbit 2.0 this affects the following parts of the API&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
- namespace registration&lt;br/&gt;
- node type registration&lt;br/&gt;
- workspace creation/removal&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
based on a issue reported by david (&amp;quot;currently an anonymous user can write the namespace registry which is probably&lt;br/&gt;
undesirable [...]&amp;quot;), we could at least add some minimal restrictions. In addition i would like to take up this discussion&lt;br/&gt;
for jsr 333.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
[1] &lt;a href=&quot;https://jsr-283.dev.java.net/issues/show_bug.cgi?id=486&quot;&gt;https://jsr-283.dev.java.net/issues/show_bug.cgi?id=486&lt;/a&gt;</description>
